BY virtue of the King's commission of the peace, oyer and terminer, and gaol-delivery of Newgate, holden for the city of London and county of Middlesex, at
Justice-hall in the Old-Bailey, before the
Right Honourable William Bridgen, Esq; Lord-Mayor of the city of London ;
Sir Richard Adams, Knt. one of the Barons of his Majesty's Court of Exchequer ;
James Eyre, Esq; Recorder , and others of his Majesty's Justices of oyer and terminer of the city of London, and gaol-delivery of Newgate, holden for the said city and county of Middlesex, on Wednesday the 7th, Thursday the 8th, Friday the 9th, Saturday the 10th, and Monday the 12th of December, in the fourth year of his Majesty's reign, six persons were capitally convicted and received sentence of death, for the several crimes in their indictments set forth, viz.
